# Testing Standards

## Testing Pyramid

- **70% Unit tests** — business logic, utils, Zod schemas, store logic, hooks
- **25% Integration tests** — API contracts, DB queries, AI pipeline with recorded responses
- **5% E2E tests** — critical user journeys (Detox)

## File Placement

Test files live next to the code they test:

```
features/meals/hooks/useMealSummary.ts
features/meals/hooks/useMealSummary.test.ts
```

## Naming

```typescript
describe('useMealSummary', () => {
  it('calculates total calories from ingredients', () => { ... });
  it('returns zero when no meals logged for the day', () => { ... });
  it('handles missing micronutrient data gracefully', () => { ... });
});
```

## Tools by Layer

| Layer | Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Unit (Mobile) | Jest + React Native Testing Library | Components, hooks, store |
| Unit (Edge Functions) | Vitest | Route handlers, business logic |
| Integration (API) | Supertest + Testcontainers | Full request lifecycle |
| Integration (AI) | pytest + VCR.py | Vision pipeline with recorded responses |
| E2E (Mobile) | Detox | Critical user journeys |
| Visual | Storybook + Chromatic | Component visual regression |

## Mocking Rules

- Mock Supabase client with `vi.mock('@supabase/supabase-js')`.
- Mock AI API calls with recorded responses (VCR cassettes). Never call real AI APIs in tests.
- Use Testcontainers for integration tests that need a real Postgres instance.
- Never mock what you're testing — mock only external boundaries.

## AI-Specific Testing

- **Prompt regression**: golden dataset of 100 meal images with expected outputs.
- **Hallucination detection**: validate nutritional claims against USDA reference data.
- **MILP correctness**: verify all hard constraints satisfied (allergens, calorie targets).
